                     <interp inst="def1-2348-18390812" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2348-18390812" type="surname" value="PULBROOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2348-18390812" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN PULBROOK</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390812-2348-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390812-2348-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390812-2348-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp> for feloniously forging and I uttering a request for the delivery of goods; and that he had been before convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1098" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1098" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1098" type="surname" value="HAYWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1098" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an ironmonger. I have bad dealings with Messrs. Warner for some years, but have not had any account with them for about eighteen months—the prisoner was in my employ, and quitted about the 12th of June—I do not think he had taken orders from me to Messrs. Warner above once or twice, but he has taken orders—this order is not one of mine—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>)—it is the prisoner's writing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1099" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1099" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1099" type="surname" value="WARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1099" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD WARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Messrs. Warner—I received this order from the prisoner, and delivered him the goods stated in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1100" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1100" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1100" type="surname" value="WARNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1100" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED WARNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the son of one of the partners, and manage their business. It is the custom in our business to deliver goods on the authority of such papers as this—we constantly do it, every day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> As between you and Mr. Hayward have you done so? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Certainly—it is the ordinary form of a request to deliver goods to Mr. Hayward, or to any body.</p>
               <p>
